So the use-case I had in mind is actually to replace the static analysis I had already written for https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container. The idea is that I can parse various Attributes to configure a dependency injection container. For example...

```php

#[Service]
interface Storage {

    public function get(string $key) : mixed;

    public function put(string $key, mixed $val) : void;

}

#[Service]
class FilesystemStorage {

    public function __construct(#[Inject('/path/to/storage/dir')] private string $dir) {}

    public function get(string $key) : mixed {
        // ...
    }

    public function put(string $key) : void {
        // ...
    }

}

class StorageConsumer {

    public function __construct(Storage $storage) {}

}
```

With this setup I could determine that when you created `StorageConsumer` with the container we should use the `FielsystemStorage` class and inject the string `/path/to/storage/dir` on object construction.

The static analysis that I have currently gets the job done but, as I'm sure you're aware, statically analyzing PHP has some pitfalls and gotchas. I would prefer to use a library that is more likely to handle those pitfalls and gotchas correctly.
